text.tspan: Change in death rates through the 20th century, United States, 1900 to
Total mortality rates by cause of death, measured as the number of deaths per 100,000 population. Death rates are given as
all-age rates (not age-standardized). Data for specific causes of death may be missing or intermittent where it enters or falls
out of the top 10 reported causes of deaths in any year.
